### How to Use in Your Odin Project (Recommended Way)

#### 1. Best & Easiest Method: Download + Self-host

1. Font download karo (free):
   - Official: https://www.joelcarrouche.com/fonts/norse
   - Alternative safe links: FontSpace, 1001Fonts, or cdnfonts.com/norse.font

2. Files extract karo → `Norse-Regular.otf` aur `Norse-Bold.otf` (ya .ttf)

3. Project folder mein ek `fonts` folder banao aur dono files wahan daal do.

#### 2. CSS Code (@font-face)

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Norse';
  src: url('fonts/Norse-Regular.otf') format('opentype');
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Norse';
  src: url('fonts/Norse-Bold.otf') format('opentype');
  font-weight: bold;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
```

#### 3. Apply in Sidebar (Odin Project Style)

```css
.sidebar .logo {
  font-family: 'Norse', sans-serif;
  font-size: 6rem;           /* Adjust according to your image */
  font-weight: bold;
  color: white;
  text-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  letter-spacing: 4px;
  line-height: 1;
}
